# Copy this file to `.env` (or `.env.test`) inside `coco-rs/tests/live/`.
# Both filenames are read; `.env.test` wins when both exist.
#
# Schema mirrors `coco-rs/vercel-ai/ai/tests/.env.example`:
# every test target is configured by a `COCO_LIVE_TEST_<PROVIDER>_<FIELD>`
# bundle, where `<PROVIDER>` upper-cases the builtin provider name with
# `-` → `_` (e.g. `OPENAI`, `ANTHROPIC`, `DEEPSEEK_OPENAI`).
#
# Recognised fields per provider:
#   API_KEY       — credential. Test-isolated; falls back to the
#                   builtin's native env_key (OPENAI_API_KEY, etc.) when
#                   unset, so existing exports keep working.
#   MODEL         — model id (required to enable the provider; tests
#                   skip with a one-line message when unset).
#   BASE_URL      — alternate gateway / mirror; leaves builtin
#                   `https://api.<provider>.com/...` when unset.
#   WIRE_API      — `responses` | `chat` (rare; openai builtin already
#                   pins `responses`).
#   CAPABILITIES  — comma list from {text, streaming, tools, compact,
#                   cross_protocol}, or `none` to disable everything for
#                   this provider. Overrides the global gate.
#
# `API_KEY`, `BASE_URL`, and `WIRE_API` are folded into a synthesized
# `providers.json` overlay applied through the same `apply_partial_layer`
# path the production resolver uses — anything legal in
# `~/.coco/providers.json` works here.
#
# `MODEL` is read directly by the test framework and threaded into
# `LiveTarget` (it's a per-call argument to `build_api_client`, not part
# of provider config).

# ============================================================================
# OpenAI Responses (gpt-5, …)
# ============================================================================
# Builtin `openai` provider already pins `wire_api: responses` — the SDK
# posts to `<base_url>/responses`. Set BASE_URL to retarget to a gateway
# (TikTok GPT proxy, Azure OpenAI, …); leave unset to hit
# `https://api.openai.com/v1`.
# COCO_LIVE_TEST_OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...
# COCO_LIVE_TEST_OPENAI_MODEL=gpt-5-2025-08-07
# COCO_LIVE_TEST_OPENAI_BASE_URL=https://genai-sg-og.tiktok-row.org/gpt/openapi/online
# COCO_LIVE_TEST_OPENAI_CAPABILITIES=text,streaming,tools

# ============================================================================
# Anthropic
# ============================================================================
# COCO_LIVE_TEST_ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...
# COCO_LIVE_TEST_ANTHROPIC_MODEL=claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929
# COCO_LIVE_TEST_ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL=https://api.anthropic.com/v1
# COCO_LIVE_TEST_ANTHROPIC_CAPABILITIES=text,streaming,tools

# ============================================================================
# Google Gemini
# ============================================================================
# Builtin `google` provider posts to `<base_url>/models/<id>:generateContent`
# and sends the credential as the `x-goog-api-key` header. Set BASE_URL to
# retarget to a Gemini-compatible gateway (Bytedance AIDP modelhub, etc.);
# leave unset to hit `https://generativelanguage.googleapis.com/v1beta`.
# COCO_LIVE_TEST_GOOGLE_API_KEY=...
# COCO_LIVE_TEST_GOOGLE_MODEL=gemini-2.5-pro
# COCO_LIVE_TEST_GOOGLE_BASE_URL=https://generativelanguage.googleapis.com/v1beta
# COCO_LIVE_TEST_GOOGLE_CAPABILITIES=text,streaming,tools

# ============================================================================
# OpenAI-compatible & Anthropic protocol coverage (DeepSeek backend)
# ============================================================================
# These two stanzas cover the two non-trivial *protocol clients* in
# coco-rs — the OpenAI-compatible HTTP client and the Anthropic-protocol
# HTTP client. DeepSeek is a convenient backend because it exposes the
# same model on both wire shapes, so a single key powers both.
#
# This is NOT a "DeepSeek as a provider" test — it's "openai-compatible
# protocol vs. anthropic protocol" parity testing. The `deepseek-*`
# builtin names just identify which builtin holds the right base_url.
#
# `DEEPSEEK_API_KEY` is the native env_key for both `deepseek-openai`
# (api: OpenaiCompat) and `deepseek-anthropic` (api: Anthropic) builtins,
# so set it once and both variants light up. The
# `COCO_LIVE_TEST_*_API_KEY` per-variant override is supported but
# almost always unnecessary.
# DEEPSEEK_API_KEY=sk-...
#
# OpenAI-compatible client (api: OpenaiCompat → api.deepseek.com/v1):
# COCO_LIVE_TEST_DEEPSEEK_OPENAI_MODEL=deepseek-v4-flash
# COCO_LIVE_TEST_DEEPSEEK_OPENAI_CAPABILITIES=text,streaming,tools,compact,cross_protocol
#
# Anthropic-protocol client (api: Anthropic → api.deepseek.com/anthropic/v1):
# COCO_LIVE_TEST_DEEPSEEK_ANTHROPIC_MODEL=deepseek-v4-flash
# COCO_LIVE_TEST_DEEPSEEK_ANTHROPIC_CAPABILITIES=text,streaming,tools,compact,cross_protocol

# ============================================================================
# Global gates
# ============================================================================
# Allow-list of providers to run (comma list, lowercase). Unset = run all.
# COCO_LIVE_TEST_PROVIDERS=openai,deepseek-openai

# Global capability filter (per-provider `*_CAPABILITIES` overrides this).
# COCO_LIVE_TEST_CAPABILITIES=text,streaming

# Custom path to this env file (overrides .env.test / .env discovery).
# COCO_LIVE_TEST_ENV_FILE=/abs/path/to/credentials.env
